  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFC Global Financial Institutions Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Given that the fund will co-invest in IFC investments, it will support private sector development by increasing access to growth capital for SMEs in Emerging Markets.   2. The fund will further enhance and expand IFC&apos;&apos;s development impact by leveraging IFC&apos;&apos;s economic capital so that IFC can make more investments and thus expand its developmental reach. 3. The fund will also allow IFC to participate in larger ticket transactions which IFC would otherwise not be able to finance from its own balance sheet.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As part of IFC&apos;&apos;s strategic focus on supporting the financial sector in emerging markets, IFC is proposing to invest in a to-be-established investment vehicle (the &quot;IFC Global Financial Institutions Fund&quot;) that will mobilize additional capital for co-investments in financial institutions operating in emerging markets.</narrative>
  </description>
